50|$|Several {{enhanced}} oil recovery technologies have been employed at Midway-Sunset. Since {{the oil is}} heavy, and does not flow freely, it can be assisted by thermal methods, which include steamflooding, cyclic steam, and <b>fire</b> <b>flooding.</b> Waterflooding {{is also used to}} boost reservoir pressures.|$|R
25|$|As of 1997, four pools – the Tulare, Etchegoin, Cahn, and Reef Ridge – {{continued}} to have active recovery operations using waterflooding, steam <b>flooding,</b> and <b>fire</b> <b>flooding.</b> As of 2008, the principal operators on the Lost Hills Field were Chevron Corp. and Aera Energy LLC.|$|R
